main event: A reported unidentified flying object was observed in Nouasseur, French Morocco on October 3, 1954, for approximately 20 seconds.
interesting points: The observation was made using a ground theodolite.
The object appeared to travel in a straight path without maneuvering.
No physical evidence or photographs were obtained.
The conclusion was that the object was unidentified.
The report came from Project Blue Book, a U.S. Air Force program that investigated UFOs.
sighted object: one unidentified flying object observed for 20 seconds
